PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (SCHEDULE NO. 932) providing for the use of calcium silicate (an anti-caking agent) to a maximum of 2.0% in the following dried egg products: dried whole egg, dried egg white (dried albumen), dried egg yolk, dried whole egg mix, and dried egg yolk mix.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 1994-0329 Publication Date: 1994-05-18
Attachments
precis:
Amendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (SCHEDULE NO. 932) providing
for the use of calcium silicate (an anti-caking agent) to a maximum of
2.0% in the following dried egg products: dried whole egg, dried egg
white (dried albumen), dried egg yolk, dried whole egg mix, and dried egg
yolk mix.
